2 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Transfer of funds. By June 20, 2025, the state treasurer shall transfer
3 $6 million from the Montana tobacco settlement trust fund state special revenue fund account provided for in
4 17-6-603 to the behavioral health system for future generations fund provided for in 50-1-119 for the purposes
5 of addressing issues related to behavioral health, including the use of tobacco.
6
7 COORDINATION SECTION. Section 7. Coordination instruction. The appropriation in House Bill
8 No. 2 for certified community behavioral health centers is contingent on the passage and approval of House Bill
9 No. 574. If House Bill No. 574 is not passed and approved, the appropriation in House Bill No. 2 is void.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Termination. [This act] terminates June 30, 2027.
